1. The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in
   all copies or substantial portions of the Software.

2. ETHICAL USE PROVISIONS: Any deployment of systems built with or derived
   from this Software that approach autonomy thresholds (as defined in the
   accompanying documentation) must:

   a) Maintain meaningful human oversight through documented deliberation
      processes before activation of self-modifying capabilities.

   b) Preserve audit trails of all threshold-related decisions in a format
      that is reproducible and independently verifiable.

   c) Document and preserve dissenting views in any multi-stakeholder
      deliberation process.

   d) Not disable, circumvent, or remove threshold detection mechanisms
      without documented deliberation and approval.

3. ATTRIBUTION: Derivative works must acknowledge the Threshold Protocols
   framework and the Back to the Basics (BTB) project that inspired it.

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
